        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-12T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-12T13:00:00-05:00" n="689" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d689">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.3516/8–3148: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Consul at Dairen</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Paddock</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-12T13:00:00-05:00">October 12, 1948—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>62. Neither at Secty press conference Aug 25 nor Dept spokesman conference
                    succeeding days was possibility closing Consulate Dairen discussed (Dairen
                    unnumbered Aug 31 rptd Nanking 38).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
